        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 4 at 2:50PM MDT by NWS Salt Lake City UT</headline>
        <description>At 249 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 20
miles northwest of Enoch, or 23 miles northwest of Cedar City, moving
east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of north central Iron
County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
